I always get this query- Can Sayesha play full song ? Yes ! In fact she learns and plays full songs only. 
So here is her full song keyboard coverage video💕 

Why this song ? What is so special about this song ? 

This song 🎵 : 
- Sayesha has been singing this song since she was 5 🎤
- This is the longest song she has learned till now ! 🎵
- The song structure is such, feels like it has 3-4 songs within it.🎼
- Different codes for different sections 🎹
- She added fillers first time 🎶
- Last but not least we recorded it in one go 😍

Please watch full video (if you like 😜) she has put her heart & soul while playing, clearly visible on her face ❤️

Music credit: @sachettandonofficial @arijitsingh 

Music teacher : @buddhi_parkash1 

#piano #pianocover #pianist #keyboard #keyboardpalyer #music #musician #sayesha

Never ever imagined in my dreams I would dance with my mini version one day 🥰

Since childhood I have been an active child, I liked music and, selflessly started dancing. I used to participate in dance competitions and won a few of them 🥰
As time went on, I grew up and chose my career in medical. Dancing became a buried hobby to me. 

Little did I know that your hobbies pass into your generation too and recently I got to know that Sayesha loves dancing, so I started dancing with her to take her hobby forward.

I see mini me in her and childishly rejoice dancing with her 💕

@dr_sanyogita 

Song credit: @nehakakkar @dhvanibhanushali22 @norafatehi

Stay tuned 💛

Outfit: @little_tags

The best decision I ever made? Keeping a long gap between my two girls. 💕

PS: Sayesha is not a second mom. She’s just a child herself and we let her be one.
We never ask her to change diapers, give showers, or feed Ayesha. She only joins in when she wants to  for the giggles, cuddles, and fun moments. She has her own space, her own life, and all the freedom she deserves.
And yes, we have a full-time nanny for Ayesha because Sayesha deserves just as much attention as Ayesha. 💗

Happy Birthday to our little cutie laddoo, Ayeshu! ♥️

Just two years ago, you came into our lives exactly as we had wished for and you’re everything we imagined and more. Your smile, your zidd, your little bursts of anger everything is wrapped in innocence and everything about you makes our world brighter 🤩

You’re the youngest, the most pampered, and definitely the most loved in the whole family. Sayesha di, Rishu bhai, and Ritansh bhai adore you like nothing else. And Mumma? Mumma’s post-work tiredness just vanishes the moment she sees your face. That bond you share with Sayesha di is pure magic.✨

Papa says his favourite part of the day is when you fall asleep in his arms and honestly, we can’t help but wonder why you didn’t come into our lives sooner.🥺

We love you endlessly, Ayesha. Hope your birthday is filled with all the Big-car-ghumi-ghumi joy you asked for! 💛
20th June !!
